body_text:
@akostadinov a combination of sed + patch files during build time, and having continuous integration for AMD GPUs will help make this less fragile and manageable from a maintainer model.
From user perspective nothing changes, their code will work on AMD or CUDA GPUs the same without any sed or modification.
we are working closely with AMD engineers to get a PR opened that is more concise.

body:
@akostadinov a combination of `sed` + patch files during build time, and having continuous integration for AMD GPUs will help make this less fragile and manageable from a maintainer model.

From user perspective nothing changes, their code will work on AMD or CUDA GPUs the same without any `sed` or modification.

we are working closely with AMD engineers to get a PR opened that is more concise.
